services.name: SeismicAPI
services.description:
This is the main service for managing and querying metadata and seismic traces from Cognite Data Fusion (CDF). [`Survey`](#com.cognite.seismic.v1.survey) and [`Partition`](#com.cognite.seismic.v1.partition) objects are primarily metadata-focused, and all seismic traces are queried via references to [`SeismicStore`](#com.cognite.seismic.v1.seismicstore) or [`Seismic`](#com.cognite.seismic.v1.seismic) objects.

Queries are divided into these broad categories:
- **Management**: Creating, editing and deleting Cognite Data Fusion objects, as well as managing the status of file uploading and processing.
- **Metadata**: Information about surveys, partitions, seismic objects, and headers.
- **Trace**: Retrieving traces or information about traces.

methods.name: CreateSurvey
methods.description:
Creates a Survey object in the data model. A Survey object represents a grouping of seismic data
in the same area and normally shares acquisition and most processing parameters.

Capabilities: Requires Seismic:WRITE capability to the CDF tenant.

methods.name: SearchSurveys
methods.description:
Lists all surveys accessible to the client.
You can also choose to receive a list of Seismic and SeismicStore object ids associated with the surveys.

The returned surveys can also be limited to those that satisfy one or both of these criteria:
  - Coverage polygon of files in the survey are within an area delimited by a specified polygon.
  - Filters on metadata of both the survey and the file.

methods.name: EditSurvey
methods.description:
Modifies the metadata for a survey.

The survey crs and grid transformation can only be modified if there are no ingested seismic stores in the survey.

methods.name: DeleteSurvey
methods.description: Deletes a specified survey. Must have Seismic:ALL scope and Write capability.

methods.name: RegisterSourceSegyFile
methods.description: Registers a new file in a (previously registered) survey as source for ingestion.

methods.name: EditSourceSegyFile
methods.description:
Edits a registered source file.

Before editing, there must be no ingestion jobs running for the source file.
The SeismicStore associated with the source file must also be deleted if it was successfully created.
This request will fail if the above criteira aren't met.

methods.name: UnregisterSourceSegyFile
methods.description:
Unregisters a file previously registered as the source for ingestion.

Before unregistering, there must be no ingestion jobs running for the source file.
The SeismicStore associated with the source file must also be deleted if it was successfully created.
This request will fail if the above criteira aren't met.

methods.name: IngestSourceSegyFile
methods.description: Requests queueing of a registered file for ingestion.

methods.name: CreateSeismic
methods.description:
Creates new Seismics and assign them to partitions.
Seismic objects are mostly immutable aside from their name and metadata.
A Seismic object must be deleted and recreated in order to change properties such as the cutout or the source seismic store.

methods.name: SearchSeismics
methods.description:
Returns metadata for a Seismic object.
Can optionally retrieve seismic store & partition info if user has appropriate scope and capability.

methods.name: EditSeismic
methods.description:
Edits the specified seismic. Seismic object names and metadata can be changed.
Other properties such as the cutout, owning partition, or source seismic store can't be changed.
The seismic object must be deleted and recreated in order to modify these immutable properties.

methods.name: DeleteSeismic
methods.description: Deletes seismic objects.

methods.name: SearchSeismicStores
methods.description: Searches and retrieves seismic stores. Can only retrieve seismic stores you own.

methods.name: InspectIngestion
methods.description:
Inspects the seismicstore resulting from a possibly failed ingestion. Useful for 
debugging failed ingestions.

methods.name: EditSeismicStore
methods.description: Sets the name or metadata of a seismic store object.

methods.name: DeleteSeismicStore
methods.description: Deletes a seismic store. If any seismic objects still reference the specified seismic store, the request will fail.

methods.name: CreatePartition
methods.description: Creates a data partition, optionally setting a name.

methods.name: SearchPartitions
methods.description: Returns the specified partitions, with the same search options as the other search endpoints.

methods.name: EditPartition
methods.description: Edits partitions. The only modifiable field is the name.

methods.name: DeletePartition
methods.description: Deletes the specified partition and returns a response if it was successfully deleted.

methods.name: GetVolume
methods.description:
Requests a volume of traces by range of inlines, crosslines, and time.

**Deprecated** - use StreamTraces instead.

methods.name: GetVolumeBounds
methods.description:
Return information about what a GetVolume request would return, including bounding boxes of
trace header values, and estimated total size.
**Deprecated** - use `GetTraceBounds` instead.

methods.name: StreamTraces
methods.description:
Requests a set of seismic traces by ranges of trace headers, such as inline, crossline (for 3d),
cdp, or shotpoint (for 2d). Can also filter by geometry, and select a subset of depth indices.
See StreamTracesRequest for more information.

methods.name: GetTraceBounds
methods.description:
Returns information about what a StreamTraces request would return, including bounding boxes of
trace header values, and estimated total size.

methods.name: GetSegYFile
methods.description:
Fetches seismic data in SEG-Y format.
Each response in the stream contains a byte array that must be written, in order, to a file-like object
to produce a valid SEG-Y file. The ordering of traces in the resulting SEG-Y file is undefined.

The request object can be used to specify whether the file should contain the whole set
of traces in the source dataset or a subset of the traces (for example, a cropped file). See
[`SegYSeismicRequest`](#segyseismicrequest) for more information.
Returns a stream of `SegYSeismicResponse` objects, each containing a fragment of a SEG-Y
data stream.

methods.name: SearchFiles
methods.description:
Retrieves File objects describing the seismic files registered with the tenant.
Search criteria can be specified in the SearchFilesRequest, restricting the data retrieved
to a subset of the files in the tenant. See SearchFilesRequest for more information.
Returns a stream of file objects, terminating once all files matching the search criteria have been
returned.

methods.name: SearchJobStatus
methods.description: Retrieves ingestion job statuses, filtered by the specified criteria.

fields.name: target_storage_tier_name
fields.description:
[required]
Target storage tier for this file.

A storage tier is a defined facility for storing the trace data associated with a seismic volume.

[Accepted values]
Accepted values are defined by the tenant configuration, and allow for optimizing tradeoffs between storage
cost, retrieval performance, numeric precision and sampling.

Note that currently only one storage tier per trace store is supported, so ingesting an already ingested file
will result in the file's data being removed from the previously active storage tier.

enums.name: TraceHeaderField
enums.description: Enumeration of possible trace header fields used for indexing seismic objects.

values.name: ENERGY_SOURCE_POINT
values.description: Valid for 2d seismic objects. Corresponds to bytes 17-20 of standard trace header: energy source point number.

values.name: CDP
values.description: Valid for 2d seismic objects. Corresponds to bytes 21-24 of standard trace header: ensemble number.

values.name: INLINE
values.description: Valid for 3d seismic objects. Corresponds to bytes 189-192 of standard trace header: inline number.

values.name: CROSSLINE
values.description: Valid for 3d seismic objects. Corresponds to bytes 193-196 of standard trace header: crossline number.

values.name: SHOTPOINT
values.description: Valid for 2d seismic objects. Corresponds to bytes 197-202 of standard trace header: shotpoint number.

values.name: CDP_TRACE
values.description: Valid for pre-stack seismic objects. Corresponds to bytes 25-28 of standard trace header: trace number within ensemble

values.name: OFFSET
values.description: Valid for pre-stack seismic objects. Corresponds to bytes 37-40 of standard trace header: distance from center of source point to the center of receiver group.

fields.description: [optional] Position of the crossline number field in the trace headers. Defaults to 193 as per the SEG-Y rev1 specification

fields.description: [optional] Position of the X coordinate of ensemble (CDP) in trace headers. Defaults to 181 as per the SEG-Y rev1 specification

fields.name: cdp_y_offset
fields.description: [optional] Position of the Y coordinate of ensemble (CDP) in trace headers. Defaults to 185 as per the SEG-Y rev1 specification

fields.name: cdp_number_offset
fields.description: [optional] Position of the ensemble (CDP) number in trace headers. Defaults to 21 as per the SEG-Y rev1 specification

fields.description: [optional] Position of the energy source point in trace headers. Defaults to 17 as per the SEG-Y rev1 specification

fields.name: shotpoint_offset
fields.description: [optional] Position of the shotpoint field in trace headers. Defaults to 197 as per the SEG-Y rev1 specification

fields.name: cdp_trace_offset
fields.description: [optional] Position of the trace number within ensemble. Defaults to 21 as per the SEG-Y rev1 specification.

fields.name: offset_header_offset
fields.description: [optional] Position of the 'offset' field in the trace header. Defaults to 37 as per the SEG-Y rev1 specification.

fields.name: source_group_scalar_override
fields.description:
[optional] Multiplier for CDP-X and CDP-Y values that overrides the scalar factor obtained from the trace header.
Note that this is a floating point multiplier used directly to scale CDP-X and CDP-Y values, and it is not
interpreted in the way that the "source group scalar trace header field" in the SEG-Y specification is.
In other words, to divide by 100 you must specify 0.01, not -100. Negative values and values greater than 1 are not permitted.
To remove the override from a file where an override has previously been set, set the source_group_scalar_override to 0 or NaN.
The next ingestion process for that file will then use the source group scalar values found in trace headers.
